          "type": "draw",
          "qp_pages": [
            16
          ],
          "max_marks": 2,
          "ms_text": "1. Pyramid shape with 5 levels (bars) decreasing in width from bottom to top. 2. Correct labels in order: phytoplankton, krill, mackerel, cod, seal."
        },
        {
          "sub_id": "6(c)",
          "type": "text",
          "qp_pages": [
            16
          ],
          "max_marks": 2,
          "ms_text": "Pyramid of numbers can be any shape because one large producer (like a tree) can support many consumers, or parasites can increase numbers at higher levels. Pyramid of biomass is always pyramid shaped."
        },
        {
          "sub_id": "6(d)",
          "type": "text",
          "qp_pages": [
            17
          ],
          "max_marks": 4,
          "ms_text": "Variation reasons: 1. Temperature change (affects growth/reproduction). 2. Light intensity (affects photosynthesis of phytoplankton). 3. Nutrient availability. 4. Migration of species. 5. Breeding cycles."
        },
        {
          "sub_id": "6(e)",
          "type": "text",
          "qp_pages": [
            17
          ],
          "max_marks": 2,
          "ms_text": "Marine ecosystems affected by climate change: 1. Rising sea temperatures (coral bleaching/metabolism). 2. Ocean acidification (dissolving shells). 3. Rising sea levels (loss of coastal habitats)."
        }
